task: Port loader-screen from sdui-proto (orbital cyan/purple/inner + floating logo + bottom progress bar with glow). Loader is the first impression — must hit visually within 200ms of paint.

requires: [vue, vite]
source: /Users/denistka/Projects/sdui-proto/src/assets/styles/sdui.css#L573-L620
out:
  - app/src/components/loader/LoaderScreen.vue
  - app/src/components/loader/loader.css
  - app/src/components/loader/logo.svg
  - app/src/composables/useAppReady.ts

api-contract:
  props:
    - progress: number 0..1 (driven by useAppReady)
    - fadeOut: boolean (triggers exit animation)
  emits:
    - 'finished' (after fadeOut completes)

constraints:
  - DOM: .loader-screen > .orbital-container (orbital--cyan, --purple, --cyan-inner) + .loader-logo > svg + .loader-progress (track, fill, glow).
  - Keyframes ported verbatim: orbital-cyan, orbital-purple, orbital-inner, logo-float, progress glow.
  - Inline critical CSS in index.html so loader paints before main.ts boot.
  - useAppReady tracks: fonts ready, glass-tokens applied, first route resolved → resolves to 1.
  - Exit animation: scale(1.05) + opacity 0 over 600ms, then `finished` event removes from DOM.
  - Total load-to-first-view target: < 1.5s on Vercel preview (tested 4G throttle).

done:
  - Loader appears before any white-flash on cold load.
  - Orbital animations smooth at 60fps (no jank in DevTools perf panel).
  - Progress bar glow tracks `progress` prop in real time.
  - On `fadeOut=true`, scales out cleanly and emits `finished`.
  - Lighthouse "Largest Contentful Paint" element is the logo (verified).
